                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-137" type="given" value="JOHN BORLAND"></interp>JOHN BORLAND SAUNDERS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to John, George, and Fran<lb></lb>cis Rivington, booksellers, in St. Paul's-churchyard. On the night in question, when the officer came in, I missed two books, which he produced—they had been on the counter—they are two volumes of different works and are worth 21<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was in great distress—I have a wife and daughter, and had no employment for a long time.</p>
